cisco5800HealthMonMIB.name: cisco5800HealthMonMIB
cisco5800HealthMonMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-snmp@cisco.com
cisco5800HealthMonMIB.description: This MIB provides a means to monitor the status of a system's health.

ciscoHealthMonNumShelves.name: ciscoHealthMonNumShelves
ciscoHealthMonNumShelves.description: The total number of shelves monitored by the health monitor.

ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesUp.name: ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesUp
ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesUp.description: This is the total number of active T1/E1 lines across all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesDown.name: ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesDown
ciscoHealthMonNumT1E1LinesDown.description: This is the total number of inactive T1/E1 lines across all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonNumActiveDS0.name: ciscoHealthMonNumActiveDS0
ciscoHealthMonNumActiveDS0.description: The total number of DS0's in use across all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonNumTotalDS0.name: ciscoHealthMonNumTotalDS0
ciscoHealthMonNumTotalDS0.description: The total number of DS0's from all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonNumTotalModems.name: ciscoHealthMonNumTotalModems
ciscoHealthMonNumTotalModems.description: This is the total number of ciscoHealthMonTotalModems from all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonNumModemsInUse.name: ciscoHealthMonNumModemsInUse
ciscoHealthMonNumModemsInUse.description: This is the total number of ciscoHealthMonModemsInUse from all the monitored shelves .

ciscoHealthMonNumUnavailableModems.name: ciscoHealthMonNumUnavailableModems
ciscoHealthMonNumUnavailableModems.description: This is the total number of ciscoHealthMonUnavailableModems from all the monitored shelves.

ciscoHealthMonStatusTable.name: ciscoHealthMonStatusTable
ciscoHealthMonStatusTable.description: The table of status maintained by the health monitor.

ciscoHealthMonStatusEntry.name: ciscoHealthMonStatusEntry
ciscoHealthMonStatusEntry.description: An entry in the status table, containing the information about the status of the health monitoring setup commands. Depending on the configured monitoring type these commands are setup on the shelf or on the system controller. Monitoring iomem is done on the shelf where as monitoring modem and trunk is done on system controller. ciscoHealthMonShelfId, ciscoHealthMonAddress doesn't exist for the modem and trunk monitoring types since they are done on the system controller.

ciscoHealthMonStatusIndex.name: ciscoHealthMonStatusIndex
ciscoHealthMonStatusIndex.description: Unique index for indexing the ciscoHealthMonStatusTable. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.

ciscoHealthMonShelfId.name: ciscoHealthMonShelfId
ciscoHealthMonShelfId.description: This is the shelf-id of the monitored shelf.

ciscoHealthMonAddress.name: ciscoHealthMonAddress
ciscoHealthMonAddress.description: This is the IP address of the monitored shelf.

ciscoHealthMonDescr.name: ciscoHealthMonDescr
ciscoHealthMonDescr.description: Textual description of the utilization type being monitored on a shelf. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry.

ciscoHealthMonValue.name: ciscoHealthMonValue
ciscoHealthMonValue.description: The current value for the monitoring type on a monitored shelf.

ciscoHealthMonThreshold.name: ciscoHealthMonThreshold
ciscoHealthMonThreshold.description: This is the monitoring threshold value configured through the command line. If the configured monitoring type is io-mem, rmon alarm on the shelf will use this value as the threshold for generating the event. Shelf will be asked to send this generated event trap to the system controller. Once the system controller receives this trap, trap will converted to the health monitor mib format and sent to the management station. If the configured monitoring types are trunk and/or modem, ciscoHealthMonValue is compared with this value and if ciscoHealthMonValue exceeds this value, a notification is sent to the configured management station. Also, a notification will be sent to the management station if the current monitoring value is less than the configured threshold and the previous monitored value is greater than the configured threshold value.

ciscoHealthMonThresholdExceedCount.name: ciscoHealthMonThresholdExceedCount
ciscoHealthMonThresholdExceedCount.description: Number of times monitoring value exceeded the configured threshold value.

ciscoHealthMonCountTable.name: ciscoHealthMonCountTable
ciscoHealthMonCountTable.description: The table of mib entries maintained by the health monitor.

ciscoHealthMonCountEntry.name: ciscoHealthMonCountEntry
ciscoHealthMonCountEntry.description: An entry in the count table represents the polled data of ceratin mib variables for a router shelf. System controller will do the polling of the mib variables only if system controller can talk to that particular router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonCountIndex.name: ciscoHealthMonCountIndex
ciscoHealthMonCountIndex.description: Unique index for indexing the ciscoHealthMonCountTable. This unique index represents the shelf-id of the monitored shelf.

ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesUp.name: ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesUp
ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesUp.description: The number of active T1 and E1 lines on a shelf. A line is considered as an active line if it is operationally up.

ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesDown.name: ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesDown
ciscoHealthMonT1E1LinesDown.description: The number of inactive T1 and E1 lines on a shelf. This is the special case where a line is counted as down if it is operationally down and administratively up.

ciscoHealthMonActiveDS0.name: ciscoHealthMonActiveDS0
ciscoHealthMonActiveDS0.description: The number of DS0's that are currently in use.

ciscoHealthMonTotalDS0.name: ciscoHealthMonTotalDS0
ciscoHealthMonTotalDS0.description: The total number of DS0's on a shelf. This is based on the number of T1 and E1 lines present on the router shelf. Total DS0 = (# of T1 lines - 1 * 24) + 23 + (# of E1 lines*30).

ciscoHealthMonTotalModems.name: ciscoHealthMonTotalModems
ciscoHealthMonTotalModems.description: The total number of modems installed on a shelf. This is the polled value for cmSystemInstalledModem from the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonModemsInUse.name: ciscoHealthMonModemsInUse
ciscoHealthMonModemsInUse.description: The number of modems on a shelf that are in the following states: connected, offHook, loopback, or downloadFirmware. This the polled value for cmSystemModemsInUse from the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonUnavailableModems.name: ciscoHealthMonUnavailableModems
ciscoHealthMonUnavailableModems.description: The number of modems on a shelf that cannot accept the calls. They are in the following states: unknown, onHook, busiedOut, disabled, bad, or downloadFirmwareFailed. This is the polled value for cmSystemModemsUnavailable from the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonIOMemUsed.name: ciscoHealthMonIOMemUsed
ciscoHealthMonIOMemUsed.description: The number of bytes of IO memory that are currently in use by the applications on the shelf. This is the polled value for ciscoMemoryPoolUsed of io-mem type on the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonIOMemFree.name: ciscoHealthMonIOMemFree
ciscoHealthMonIOMemFree.description: The number of bytes of IO memory that are currently available to use on the shelf.This is the polled value for ciscoMemoryPoolFree of io-mem type on the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonCPUavgBusy5.name: ciscoHealthMonCPUavgBusy5
ciscoHealthMonCPUavgBusy5.description: 5 minute exponentially-decayed moving average of the CPU busy percentage. This is the polled value for avgBusy5 from the router shelf.

ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressInOctet.name: ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressInOctet
ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressInOctet.description: This is the percentage utilization of total number of octets received on all the active egress interface, including framing characters. A port is considered as an egress port if it's ifSpeed > 1544000 % Utilization of ifInOctets = (diff_total_ifInoctets*100)/ (time in seconds * total_speed) .

ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressOutOctet.name: ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressOutOctet
ciscoHealthMonUtilEgressOutOctet.description: This is the percentage utilization of the total number of octets transmitted out on all the active egress interface, including framing characters. A port is considered as an egress port if it's ifSpeed > 1544000 % Utilization of ifOutOctets = (diff_total_ifOutoctets*100)/ (time in seconds * total_speed) .

ciscoHealthMonShelfLastUpdate.name: ciscoHealthMonShelfLastUpdate
ciscoHealthMonShelfLastUpdate.description: This is the last time at which the system-controller has polled the mib entries from a shelf. However, if system-controller can not talk to that shelf, this entry will have the same time as the last update and a string Lost Contact. All the mib entries corresponding to this shelf will remain as it is until system-controller can talk to this shelf again.

ciscoHealthMonEnableNotification.name: ciscoHealthMonEnableNotification
ciscoHealthMonEnableNotification.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the ciscoHealthNotification. A false value will prevent notifications from being generated by this system.

ciscoHealthMonNotification.name: ciscoHealthMonNotification
ciscoHealthMonNotification.description: A ciscoHealthMonNotification is sent if the measured utilization has crossed the threshold value. It will be generated when the value rises above the threshold. ciscoHealthMonShelfId and ciscoHealthMonAddress are optional entries. This entry is valid only if the notification generated for the monitoring types set on the router shelf. This entry will not have anything if notification is generated for the monitoring types set on the system controller.

cisco5800HealthMonMIBCompliance.name: cisco5800HealthMonMIBCompliance
cisco5800HealthMonMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Health Monitor MIB

cisco5800HealthMonMIBGroup.name: cisco5800HealthMonMIBGroup
cisco5800HealthMonMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing health monitoring capability to a cisco chassis.
